cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.HC 

This paper involves the use of computer vision techniques to analyze images and extract information from them. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves the analysis of images related to physical attractiveness, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of search engines to gather data also involves information retrieval techniques, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the manifestation of stereotypes in different countries and regions, which involves social and cultural aspects, falling under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of stereotypes on human perception, which falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
